## 1. What’s New

### 1.1 Feature Summary

**Kiro SDLC Agents** is a new VS Code / Kiro IDE extension that brings a multi-agent SDLC pipeline directly into your workspace. With a single command, you can inject AI agent configurations for Business Analysis, Solution Architecture, QA, Development, DevOps, UI, and Security — enabling structured, AI-assisted software development workflows.

This initial release (v1.0.0) delivers the **Extension Core** — the foundation that activates the extension, registers commands, and provides visual status feedback.

### 1.2 User-Facing Changes

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Change | Description | Impact |
| 1 | Extension auto-activates on startup | Extension is always ready — no manual activation needed | Low (transparent to user) |
| 2 | 5 commands in Command Palette | Inject All, Inject Selective, Run Indexer, Update, Show Status | High (primary interaction) |
| 3 | Status bar indicator | Shows SDLC health at a glance (✓ all present, ⚠ missing, ⊘ no workspace) | Medium (passive awareness) |
| 4 | Confirmation dialogs | Prevents accidental file overwrites during inject/update | Medium (safety feature) |
| 5 | Code Intelligence Indexer | Auto-detects runtime (Python/Java/Node.js/PowerShell/Bash) and indexes codebase | High (enables AI context) |

### 1.3 Screenshots (if applicable)

Screenshots to be added after final UI verification.

## 2. Technical Changes

### 2.1 API Changes

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Type | Endpoint | Method | Description |
| New | kiroSdlc.injectAll | VS Code Command | Injects all SDLC components into workspace |
| New | kiroSdlc.injectSelective | VS Code Command | Multi-select component injection |
| New | kiroSdlc.runIndex | VS Code Command | Executes code intelligence indexer |
| New | kiroSdlc.update | VS Code Command | Updates agents (overwrites existing) |
| New | kiroSdlc.status | VS Code Command | Shows component presence status |

Note: These are VS Code commands, not HTTP APIs. The extension has no network communication.

### 2.2 Database Changes

**Not Applicable.** This is a client-side extension with no database.

### 2.3 Configuration Changes

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Property | Change Type | Description |
| kiroSdlc.autoIndex | New | Boolean setting — auto-run indexer after injection (default: true) |
| kiroSdlc.preferredIndexer | New | Enum setting — preferred indexer runtime (default: “auto”) |

### 2.4 Infrastructure Changes

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component | Change | Description |
| GitHub Actions CI | New | .github/workflows/ci.yml — build verification on push/PR |
| GitHub Actions Publish | New | .github/workflows/publish.yml — automated Marketplace publish on tag |
| VS Code Marketplace | New | Extension listing (requires publisher account setup) |
| Open VSX Registry | New | Extension listing for Kiro IDE (requires namespace claim) |

## 3. Bug Fixes

No bug fixes included in this release. This is the initial release (v1.0.0).

## 4. Known Issues & Limitations

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | Issue | Impact | Workaround | Target Fix |
| 1 | Publisher ID is placeholder (your-publisher-id) | Cannot publish to Marketplace until changed | Update package.json before publishing | KSA-11 |
| 2 | Repository URL is placeholder | Marketplace listing shows wrong link | Update package.json before publishing | KSA-11 |
| 3 | Only first workspace folder used in multi-root | Multi-root workspace users only get injection in first folder | Open target folder as primary workspace | Future enhancement |
| 4 | Status bar doesn’t auto-refresh | If files are deleted externally, status bar may be stale | Run “Show Status” command to refresh | Future enhancement |
| 5 | Indexer timeout fixed at 120s | Very large codebases may timeout | Run indexer manually with longer timeout | Future enhancement |

