## 6. Migration Notes

### 6.1 Data Migration

No data migration required. This is a fresh installation — the extension creates new files in the workspace only when explicitly triggered by the user.

### 6.2 Breaking Changes

No breaking changes in this release. Fully backward compatible.

This is the initial release — there is no previous version to break compatibility with.

### 6.3 Backward Compatibility

* **VS Code:** Compatible with VS Code ^1.85.0 and all newer versions
* **Kiro IDE:** Compatible with Kiro IDE (VS Code Extension Host compatible)
* **Node.js:** Extension Host runs on Node.js 20.x (bundled with VS Code)
* **Operating Systems:** Windows, macOS, Linux (all platforms supported by VS Code)

